<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-191-278  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 191 278.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Feb 19 1990 v218 n8 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Prospects dim for MFJ reform. (Modified Final Judgementrestrictions on Bell regional holding companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A draft bill to ease restrictions imposed by the Modified FinalJudgement (MFJ) on Bell regional holding companies will probablynot go forward during 1990.andP;  The draft bill, released Feb 9, 1990,has so many restrictions that even the Bell regional holdingcompanies are less enthusiastic.andP;  A short congressional work year,the complexity of the issues and strong opposition from majorindustry groups also contributed to the draft's setback.andP;  Thelegislation does not have widespread support from the House ofRepresentatives or the Telecommunications Association.andP;  MCICommunications Corp calls the legislation unnecessary and adeterrent to US preeminence in the market.andP;  The draft does containproposals that should encourage support, including provisions fornew electronic information services and the ability to conductresearch and development.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. CongressTelecommunicationsLegislationLegal IssuesBell Regional Holding CompaniesCompetitionGovernment Regulation.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>